<h1>Rails Views: Using ERB</h1>

<p>Welcome to your ERB practice page! Use this view to experiment with the concepts from the lesson.</p>

<!-- Example 1: Basic substitution tag -->
<h2>Basic Substitution</h2>
<p><%= "I love " + "Ruby!!" %></p>

<!-- Example 2: Math in ERB -->
<p>What is 1 + 1? <%= 1 + 1 %></p>

<!-- Example 3: HTML wrapping -->
<h3><%= "I love Ruby!!" %></h3>

<!-- Example 4: Scripting tags with conditional logic -->
<h2>Conditional Logic</h2>
<% if 1 == 2 %>
  <p>1 equals 2.</p>
<% else %>
  <p>1 does not equal 2.</p>
<% end %>

<!-- Example 5: Iteration -->
<h2>Iteration Example</h2>
<% squares = [1, 4, 9, 16] %>
<ul>
  <% squares.each do |square| %>
    <li><%= square %></li>
  <% end %>
</ul>

<!-- Example 6: Wall posts simulation -->
<h2>Wall Posts Example</h2>
<% wall_posts = ["First post!", "Second post!", "Hello, it's your mother. Why don't you ever call me?"] %>
<ul>
  <% wall_posts.each do |post| %>
    <li><%= post %></li>
  <% end %>
</ul>

